      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>Hey {first_name, \"there\"},</p><p>I have to be honest with you: this is a <em>terrible</em> newsletter. And the reasons why are useful I think. If you can endure a newsletter full of self-flagellation (which sounds like the sort of specialist journal that might make you a bit of cash on Substack…), we can explore together what makes a good newsletter by counter-example.</p><p>My work on newsletters with publishers makes it clear to me:</p><ol><li>What's wrong with the newsletter version of <em>OM&amp;HB</em></li><li>How I could fix it</li></ol><p>But finding the time to do that would be a challenge…</p>"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "What makes a great newsletter? We're still figuring that out, but there's enough good research and evidence out there about engaging people via email to make it clear I'm doing something very wrong. People ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "never",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " respond to mine like those over-excited folks in the lead image… ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Like many people who work in education and training, sometimes my courses amount to “do what I say, not what I do”. I was reminded of that during the first week of ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
